  "text": "This investigation strongly corroborates evidence from an earlier regional program evaluation indicating that parent education, delivered in the hospital by maternity nurses, reduces a newborn's risk of sustaining an abusive head injury resulting from shaking during the first year of life. [CITATION_1] The success of the 2 regional programs prompted a statewide expansion, and it is reasonable to assume that similar programs in all states would decrease the nationwide incidence of shaking injuries. Several states besides New York have already taken steps to adopt such programs. 30 Given the potentially devastating consequences of these injuries, the high societal costs, the program's effectiveness, and the trivial per-patient program costs, the most important issue left to debate is the best way to achieve broad implementation. ",
